<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Arduino Project – Obstacle Avoiding Robot</title>

  <style>
    /* ===== COLOR THEME (BLUE TECH) ===== */
    :root{
      --bg:#0a1020;
      --card:#111a33;
      --text:#e6ebff;
      --muted:#9aa4c7;
      --accent:#3b82f6;
      --border: rgba(255,255,255,.08);
      --radius:16px;
    }

    body{
      margin:0;
      font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height:1.6;
    }

    header{
      padding:32px 0;
      text-align:center;
      border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a1020, #0e1630);
    }

    h1{
      margin:0;
      font-size:36px;
      color:var(--accent);
    }

    .sub{
      color:var(--muted);
      margin-top:6px;
    }

    .container{
      width:min(1000px, 90%);
      margin:40px auto;
    }

    section{
      background: var(--card);
      padding:24px;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      margin-bottom:24px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
    }

    h2{
      margin-top:0;
      font-size:22px;
      border-left:4px solid var(--accent);
      padding-left:12px;
    }

    ul{
      padding-left:20px;
    }

    li{
      margin-bottom:8px;
      color:var(--muted);
    }

    p{
      color:var(--muted);
    }

    .grid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap:16px;
    }

    .badge{
      display:inline-block;
      background: rgba(59,130,246,.15);
      color: var(--accent);
      padding:6px 14px;
      border-radius:999px;
      font-size:13px;
      margin-bottom:10px;
      font-weight:600;
    }

    .btn{
      display:inline-block;
      margin-top:10px;
      padding:10px 18px;
      border-radius:12px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), #60a5fa);
      color:#fff;
      font-weight:700;
      text-decoration:none;
      transition: transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;
    }

    .btn:hover{
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(59,130,246,.35);
    }

    pre{
      background:#0a1020;
      color:#c7d2fe;
      padding:14px;
      border-radius:12px;
      overflow-x:auto;
      font-size:14px;
      border:1px solid var(--border);
    }

    footer{
      text-align:center;
      color:var(--muted);
      padding:24px;
      border-top:1px solid var(--border);
      background:#0a1020;
    }

    @media(max-width:700px){
      .grid{
        grid-template-columns:1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>Arduino Obstacle-Avoiding Robot</h1>
  <p class="sub">Autonomous robot using Arduino Uno & ultrasonic sensors</p>
  <p class="sub">Built by Abdulrhman Khablil</p>
</header>

<div class="container">

  <section>
    <span class="badge">Overview</span>
    <h2>Project Description</h2>
    <p>
      This Arduino project demonstrates an autonomous robot capable of detecting
      and avoiding obstacles using an ultrasonic sensor. The robot continuously
      measures distance and intelligently changes direction to avoid collisions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <div>
      <span class="badge">Hardware</span>
      <h2>Components Used</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Arduino Uno</li>
        <li>HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor</li>
        <li>L298N Motor Driver</li>
        <li>DC Motors & Wheels</li>
        <li>Robot Chassis</li>
        <li>Battery Pack</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <span class="badge">Software</span>
      <h2>Tools & Libraries</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Arduino IDE</li>
        <li>C / C++</li>
        <li>NewPing Library</li>
        <li>Serial Monitor</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="badge">Working</span>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The ultrasonic sensor emits a sound pulse.</li>
      <li>The echo time is converted into distance.</li>
      <li>If distance is less than 20 cm, the robot stops.</li>
      <li>The robot turns and finds a clear path.</li>
      <li>Otherwise, it moves forward continuously.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="badge">Logic</span>
    <h2>Algorithm</h2>
    <pre>
loop():
  distance = readUltrasonic()

  if distance &lt; 20 cm:
      stopMotors()
      turnLeft()
  else:
      moveForward()
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="badge">Demo</span>
    <h2>Project Demo</h2>
    <p>Explore the source code or watch the robot in action.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="#">View Arduino Code</a>
    <a class="btn" href="#" style="margin-left:10px;">Watch Demo Video</a>
  </section>

</div>

<footer>
  Built by RoboForge Robotics Club • Arduino Project
</footer>

</body>
</html>
